🚀 Azure AI Text Analytics with Python

This project demonstrates how to use Azure Cognitive Services - Text Analytics API with Python. It connects to the Azure AI service, authenticates using environment variables, and performs language detection on user-provided text.

📂 Project Structure
.
├── rest-client/
│   ├── sdk-client.py       # Python script to connect and analyze text
│   ├── .env                # Environment variables (endpoint, key)
│   └── requirements.txt    # Python dependencies
└── README.md

⚙ Features

✅ Connects to Azure Cognitive Services

✅ Uses Text Analytics API for language detection

✅ Reads API Key & Endpoint from .env file

✅ Interactive CLI to analyze text input

* Prerequisites

An Azure Subscription with Cognitive Services enabled

Python 3.8+ installed

Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt


requirements.txt

azure-ai-textanalytics
python-dotenv

📌 Setup

Create a .env file in your project folder and add your Azure credentials:

AI_SERVICE_ENDPOINT="https://<your-resource-name>.cognitiveservices.azure.com/"
AI_SERVICE_KEY="<your-api-key>"


Run the Python client:

python sdk-client.py

🖥️ Usage

Example run:

Enter some text ("quit" to stop): hello  

Language: English

📘 Learning Objectives

Learn how to authenticate with Azure Cognitive Services

Use the Azure Text Analytics SDK in Python

Detect language from user input text
